Colombian Stock Movers: Conconcreto, Grupo Aval, Grupo Nutresa

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-08-12T21:11:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/colombian-stock-movers-cementos-argos-grupo-aval-bancolombia.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 5 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index climbed 1.1 percent to 13,413.84, while the
Colcap Index added 0.7 percent to 1,611.13.  Conconcreto SA (CONCONC CB), a Colombian construction
company, rose 1.3 percent to 1,520 pesos. Gray cement sales in
 Colombia  rose 17.4 percent in June from a year ago, the national
statistics agency said in a report yesterday.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA, Colombia’s
biggest financial holding company, gained 1.7 percent to 1,220
pesos. The central bank said in minutes today of its July 29
monetary policy meeting that the country’s growth is expected to
accelerate in the second half of the year. Colombia will likely
grow between 4.5 percent and 6.5 percent this year and next,
according to the minutes.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA CB), Colombia’s biggest food
producer, rose 0.8 percent to 21,900 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  